This is one of the last projects I worked on with Task One.  My first thought was to cancel this release, and postpone it for a much later date.  But then I thought about what Task would have said and wanted, and it would have been somewhere along the lines of "Dude, I made them... sell them." So we're going to still do today's St. Patrick's Day release, but with all proceeds going to his family's GoFundMe.  The link is in my bio if you're able to donate more.  These are going up at 3 PM PST. www.stolleart.com

Micro-Shard (Shamrock)
Edition of 75
Price $20 + Shipping

After the sale is over, I will be making an immediate donation to his GoFundMe. 

Thank you for the support!

One of my favorite memories of him was when he was walking ahead of us as we strolled through the city. Piper noticed he was alone and ran up to grab his hand. They walked and talked and had a moment that night. He loved my kids and family like we were his own. This doesn’t make sense but I wouldn’t trade my memories with him for anything. RIP brother.
@frankkozik @jermainerogersart
That time Piper had a good butt question for @frankkozik @skozik13

Frank’s death is still very fresh to me and hard on my heart. Yesterday I was ok. Today was worse. I will be at Frank’s memorial next Saturday. Hoping it helps to grieve with others who loved him. @frankkozik @skozik

Mood Shard will be available at DCON Booth #310.  This 3” Shard was one of the last projects that I worked on with my friend, Task One.  What’s special about this 3” Shard is that you don’t need a hair dryer or the sun to change its colors.  All you need is a simple touch, and the colors change instantly.  These will be sold via lottery on VIP Friday night and Saturday morning.  Edition of 55. $100 each. Swipe right for video.

Have you been naughty or nice this year? 
·
The Naughty or Nice Nano Shard release will be available in collaboration with NTWRK. Each set comes with 6 x Nanos tucked snuggly into their very own stocking. 
·
Most people will get coal (black) in their stocking. Don’t act surprised, you know what you did this year. But those who’ve been nice will get a chase set (3 x red and 3 x green). 
·
Edition size is 150 sets. 
·
Tune in to NTWRK during DCon to secure a set! 

I’ll be going live on Friday the 15th at 6 PM, Saturday the 15th at 11 AM and Sunday at 11 AM. Each set is $50. Swipe right!

The legacy lives on…
21 years ago, Bounty Hunter released the original Smorkin’ Labbit. This Friday at @designercon , the Kozik Estate - booth 413 - will release a very special Legacy Labbit resin edition limited to only 61 figures split between two colorways…Spirit and Ether.

Saturday, 4-5pm, join us at the main stage to  honor Frank. We look forward to hearing your best Kozik stories and memories. 

Love,
Sharon K.
